  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nWe'd like to carry on with https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/739 and draft a support for Starknet contract testing.\r\n\r\nCairo-rs – the Rust implementation of the Cairo VM – is getting [more and more ready](https://twitter.com/ClassLambda/status/1575605473671192576), so it is a good time to work on this integration.\r\n\r\nAs discussed with @mattsse we have two options for this:\r\n- work on isolating a `Runtime` trait and a `Compiler` trait to be able to swap a `ethers-rs` implementation with a `cairo-rs` implementation\r\n- target only the `forge test` command to get it to work on starknet contracts, hacking our way into the codebase\r\n\r\nWe'd rather go for the second solution to get a first taste of what it will look like in the better-structured first option.\n\n### Additional context\n\nWe are hosting a hacking week in Lisbon at the end of Oct'22 prior to the [starknet.cc conference](https://www.starknet.cc/).\r\nCore ecosystem members will attend and spend some time building on Starknet projects.\r\nHaving a Forge-grade test runner for Starknet is an ambitious but achievable subject we'd like to hack on during these few days.",
